Trend 2: Account-Based Marketing Becomes Mainstream
Account-Based Marketing (ABM) has evolved from a niche strategy used by enterprise-focused companies to a mainstream approach embraced by organizations of all sizes. In 2026, ABM is not just a trendit's becoming table stakes for serious B2B organizations.

ABM flips the traditional marketing funnel on its head. Instead of casting a wide net to capture as many leads as possible, ABM focuses on identifying high-value target accounts and delivering highly coordinated, multi-channel campaigns designed specifically for those accounts. This requires alignment between sales and marketing teams, sophisticated targeting capabilities, and coordinated messaging across channels.

Why is ABM gaining traction? The data speaks for itself. Organizations implementing ABM strategies report higher deal values, shorter sales cycles, and improved customer lifetime value. More importantly, ABM creates stronger alignment between sales and marketing teams because both are focused on the same high-value targets.

How can you get started with ABM in 2026? The first step is identifying your ideal customer profile and the high-value accounts that match that profile. Next, develop a deep understanding of the key decision-makers within those accounts, their challenges, and their buying process. Finally, create coordinated campaigns across email, content, social media, and direct outreach designed to move these accounts through your sales pipeline.

