Trend 7: Install Base Targeting and Customer Expansion
While much attention is paid to acquiring new customers, smart organizations in 2026 are also focusing on extracting greater value from their existing customer base. Install base targetingidentifying expansion opportunities within current customershas become a significant revenue driver.

Your existing customers already trust you. They've already solved their initial problem. The question is: what other challenges are they facing that your solution suite can address? Are there additional departments or business units that could benefit from your products or services? Are there advanced features or complementary solutions they haven't yet adopted?

Organizations are using account-based approaches to identify expansion opportunities within their customer base, creating specialized campaigns targeted at existing customers with tailored messaging around new solutions or advanced capabilities. This approach often yields higher conversion rates and faster sales cycles than new customer acquisition.

Email marketing plays a critical role in expansion strategies, particularly when segmented and personalized to speak to specific use cases or departments. Rather than sending generic product announcements to your entire customer base, successful organizations send targeted messages to specific customer segments about solutions relevant to their needs.

The beauty of install base targeting is that it often delivers better margins than new customer acquisition while also improving customer lifetime value and reducing churn. Customers who expand with you are significantly more likely to remain long-term advocates.

